how me that horizon, promise me a world better than this on the other side of the sun.', 6422, 0), (132433, 'We must love one another whether or not we die.Love can’t block a bulletbut it can’t be destroyed by one either,and love is, for the most part, what makes Us Us—in Orlando and in Brooklyn and in Kabul.We will be everywhere, always;there’s nowhere else for Us, or you, to go.Anywhere you run in this world, love will be there to greet you.Around any corner, there might be two men. Kissing.', 22201, 0), (132434, 'People make moves like the Pawn.(Let''s go in the real world, look how they walk, from one up two max blocks they can take... so far it''s sounds like the moves of pawn. People can be the king and the queen...)', 4605, 0), (132435, 'The world from it self is a brutal one.', 4605, 0), (132436, 'The world will become only as great a place to live in as we make it.', 11221, 0), (132437, 'When the world turns chaotic, we must be the better part of chaos.', 21615, 0), (132438, 'i wish you could understand me, but of course it is not the way of this world that we are ever completely understood.', 2577, 0), (132439, 'It is my wish and most cherished hope that God would be pleased with my legacy, that lives would be changed by it, and that the world would be immeasurably better because I was privileged to leave a legacy at all. And if perchance I am fortunate enough to have these things come to pass, I can then rest in the fact that I have lived well.', 4397, 0), (132440, 'Life is a concoction of fatal determinism and the footsteps of us all.', 25305, 0), (132441, 'The world is one Matrix, you don''t realise it but it''s the truth. It''s well shown in the films like Matrix 1,2,3 and Inception!', 4605, 0), (132442, 'I’d won the worldbut like aforsaken explorer,I’d lostmy map.', 164, 0), (132443, 'For me,you are fresh waterthat falls from treeswhen it has stopped raining. For me, you are cinnamon that lingers on the tongue and givesbitter wordssweetening.For me, you are the scent of violins and visionof valleys smiling.And still,for me, your loveliness never ends.It traverses the worldand finds its way back to me.Only me.', 3588, 0), (132444, 'The only thing necessary in this world is love. Everything else is secondary.', 3588, 0), (132445, 'O brave new world,That has such people in ’t!-Miranda', 13, 0), (132446, 'In a world of lovelightning and rainbow are lovers now. They arc and strike upon the horizon of credence to rise above their cloudy vow', 2760, 0), (132447, 'That is one good thing about this world…there are always sure to be more springs.', 250, 0), (132448, 'Because you made me feel, Flick. Everyone is so predictable, but you? You showed up and rocked my world.', 14666, 0), (132449, '[Letter to William Ward, 11 July 1878]Dear Boy, Why don’t you write to me? I don’t know what has become of you.As for me I am ruined. The law suit is going against me and I am afraid I will have to pay costs, which means leaving Oxford and doing some horrid work to earn bread. The world is too much for me.However, I have seen Greece and had some golden days of youth. I go back to Oxford immediately for viva voce and then think of rowing up the river to town with Frank Miles. Will you come? YoursOscar', 40, 0), (132450, 'If I send all the books that I faithfully wrote overseas, would that, for any chance, be considered work-shipping??', 5065, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (132451, 'What interest hath this empty world in me? and what is there in it that may seem so lovely, as to entice my desires and delight from thee, or make me loth to come away? When I look about me with a deliberate, undeceived eye, methinks this world is a howling wilderness, and most of the inhabitants are untamed, hideous monsters. All its beauty I can wink into blackness, and all its mirth I can think into sadness ; I can drown all its pleasures in a few penitent tears, and the wind of a sigh will scatter them away (650).', 11465, 0), (132452, 'We live in relative world with relatives.', 4605, 0), (132453, 'How you see the world may not be how others view it.', 11173, 0), (132454, 'We may reconcile ourselves to the world at our peril, but it will never reconcile itself to us. . . . This unwillingness to die, doth actually impeach us of high treason against the Lord : is it not a choosing of earth before him ; and taking these present things for our happiness, and consequently asking them our very God (469)?', 11465, 0), (132455, 'All the world’s a stage, and all the men and women merely players. William Shakespeare', 15872, 0), (132456, 'Whatever you acknowledgement gains the legitimacy to exist within your world.', 11173, 0), (132457, 'Everything goes and happens fast. That''s how the world is build! (Pet Semetary 1 by Stephen King)', 4605, 0), (132458, 'I believe that the world is one strong matrix, to get out of it you can''t safe somebody unless you make it such way so you both die. I believe then... at that moment you are out of the Matrix, but it''s just kind of paradox which is 50-50.', 4605, 0), (132459, 'Some people live disconnected, in a world of their own. Their wishful thinking represents their sole veracity. But when the mirror smashes the reflection of their delusion, it will not falter to talk back. ( "The day the mirror was talking back" )', 2711, 0), (132460, 'To love at a distance and