INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (133701, 'The most valuable gift you can give to humanity is a good example.', 3337, 0), (133702, 'But could words bethe end of me?', 3805, 0), (133703, 'Never knew the word Goodbye could scatter my heart into pieces. Just 1 word, could made me cry over you.', 25476, 0), (133704, 'You can''t wake up miserable and expect something outside yourself to change that mood, you have to be willing to change that mood so you expect the best from your outside world.', 3305, 0), (133705, 'Sometimes he does talk back, but sometimes he doesn’t. Sometimes he’s not there; and from time to time I believe this was all nothing but imaginary.', 3805, 0), (133706, 'So much of who I was then I''m not today, I''ve changed for the better through the years, I''ve grown spiritually. I look at people differently, everyone is unique in their own special way', 15338, 0), (133707, 'Logan felt it, even if he wanted to deny it. His pupils were dilated and he stared at her like she was chocolate and tomorrow was the first day of Lent. Sure, she might be forbidden, but no one could withstand temptation forever. Not when it was so close. The car roared to life as Logan started it back onto the road. So he thought to ignore the attraction? Good luck. He might be a rule follower, but Sofia wasn’t. He didn’t stand a chance in hell.', 16206, 0), (133708, 'It''s a crime, when you think about how little time we get, that a man should ever be bored. When you are lying on your death bead, I expect you regret those weeks wasted more than your worst mistakes.', 1466, 0), (133709, 'I will toil under sun for what I want.', 2878, 0), (133710, 'Don''t let your journey fade. It''s God''s way of reminding us that we need him in our lives and it''s not wrong', 15338, 0), (133711, 'A Godless life is a goalless life.', 3337, 0), (133712, 'Your best - no matter how great - isnothing if you minus God from theequation.', 3337, 0), (133713, 'As he stood in the darkness, his eyes glistened and that’s when I knew my light found its traction.', 3805, 0), (133714, 'I danced as he twirled in and out of consciousness, and there we were, one in love and the other astray.', 3805, 0), (133715, 'I’ve spent awhile trying to figure out where I’m going and the only thing I’ve come to realize is it doesn’t matter where, it’s how I get there.', 3805, 0), (133716, 'May God strengthen you for a great work.', 2878, 0), (133717, 'People may forget the quantity of your works but cannot forget the quality of your works.', 3337, 0), (133718, 'All that you need to be successful and significant in life is in and around you.', 3337, 0), (133719, 'Some people must dream broadly and guilelessly, if only to balance those who never dream at all.', 19147, 0), (133720, 'Before and after you do your best, know it that you must rely on God. Your best - no matter how great - is nothing if you minus God from the equation.', 3337, 0), (133721, 'I think that the behavior of M. Alexis Tsípras is a chance for the European Union to question itself about what is wrong about the Europe of Euro, and to measure the human sufferings caused by a policy that is first and foremost monetarily driven and is wrong. In a just and democratic society, the citizen and his rights are center stage, not the economy.', 25477, 0), (133722, 'Some people make you want to be a better person, and that, for me, is the purest form of love.', 523, 0), (133723, 'she...let the blood spill down instead of tears.', 39, 0), (133724, 'Sometimes he wondered if he did these things just to test himself. To see if the feelings had gone. But they had not. When he saw her, he wanted to be with her; when he was with her, he ached to touch her; when he touched even her hand, he wanted to embrace her. He wanted to feel her against him the way he had in the attic. He wanted to know the taste of her skin and the smell of her hair. He wanted to make her laugh. He wanted to sit and listen to her talk about books until his ears fell off. But all these things he could not want, because they were things he could not have, and wanting what you could not have led to misery and madness.', 39, 0), (133725, 'He who discovers the light, discovers life. He who discovers the dark, discovers death, Neither are wrong and neither are right; your perception is what will guide your path. Our minds are our tools, our hearts our truth and our instinct our guidance, don''t let them fool you.', 3305, 0), (133726, 'Religion is what you do with your solitude.', 19164, 0), (133727, 'Someone''s therapist knows all about you.', 3805, 0), (133728, 'When you look in the mirror, do you look at yourself or for yourself?', 3805, 0), (133729, 'I love you, but there will be a dozen more too.', 3805, 0), (133730, 'What writing means to me?-Releasing my wolves...(Natasa Alina Culea)', 25478, 0), (133731, 'While you''re waiting on opportunity, it might be waiting on you to come to it. Get up and go get it!', 4098, 0), (133732, 'By all means, tell the cops about the crazy robot lady with the black leather body suit and the Kill Bill sword. Hope you like straitjackets.', 25433, 0), (133733, 'Becoming a man means doing the right thing even though it may be hard or difficult. Boys do what is easiest. A man does what is right, whether easy or not.', 23450, 0), (133734, 'Somewhere, someone is search for the pieces of you that mold well with theirs.', 3305, 0), (133735, 'Did you seriously just use the word ''loins''?', 25433, 0), (133736, 'Sure, he might not have been perfect, but if I thought he was, isn’t that all that matters?', 3805, 0), (133737, 'No matter what life throws at you, never stop loving it. Obstacles are meant to be conquered.', 166, 0), (133738, 'Sometimes you can miss the boat and find a new life.', 2538, 0), (133739, 'Aspirations without preparations will simply give you life full of frustrations. Develop yourself today!', 3337, 0), (133740, 'Only you can know the difference between your wants and your needs, and your sacrifice of your life''s time to both.', 23450, 0), (133741, 'Jack, be nimble, Jack, be quickJill''s a little whore and her alibis are dirty tricks', 8350, 0), (133742, 'Your success and significance in life is tied to the unleashing of the greatness in you.', 3337, 0), (133743, 'As time heads towards the cliff of the unknown, there are those who will be hated and pushed to the fringes. Those who look inward will have the advantage; seeking fulfillment anywhere else will only lead to a dead end and disillusionment. Those who are marginalized, are also uniquely gifted- focus on those gifts that will speak to the truth of the matter and stand your ground. Your intuition and consciousness bears light to the truth.', 25346, 0), (133744, 'Read and write. That''s the recipe for being a writer.', 25433, 0), (133745, 'My imagination and power are limitless. Nothing can stop me from achieving my dreams.', 25479, 0), (133746, 'Newly-born books are like birds… they shouldn’t be kicked out of the nest until they’re capable of flying. Wendy Anne Darling 5-1-15', 25480, 0), (133747, 'Reading teaches us the nuances of humanity. To find the beauty of what is moral and ethical in your own actions and discover the strange subtlety of what it is to question why you should exist.', 23450, 0), (133748, 'Searching through Monster.com while on the clock feels like being on Tinder while still married.', 953, 0), (133749, 'Once I had opened a book and read its pages, those characters could never be taken away from me. Even if the books were burned, they would still live on in my mind.', 15433, 0), (133750, 'There''s something beautiful about facing tragedy, you crack open a new, you find yourself in the parts of you; that can finally be explored freely with out judgement or guilt. Where to from here doesn''t exist & your not sure when it will return, but there''s something beautiful in facing tragedy, a new type of being within you is born and one whom is more fearless than ever before.', 3305, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (133751, 'life - your gunna meet some two faced people, some bosses that make your soul cringe, some places you wished you''d never walked into... But then you''ll grow, you''ll learn that your gut instinct isn''t nieve, your boss can '' fuck it'' because your dreams are more important and the places you walked into unaware of chaos, will bring you to places of perfect peace. Hold on, the struggle won''t last forever.', 3305, 0), (133752, 'I could give up, it''s the easiest optionBut what would I achieve? Many sleepless nights holding regretOf all I didn''t seek, That option will never exist to me; My dreams are far too real, Down the hard road I findMy place in the world; the closest To home Ill ever feel.', 3305, 0), (133753, 'Old is old at any age. Old is when you quit asking questions about this, that, and everything. Old is when you forget how to love-or worse, don''t care. Old is when you don''t want to dance anymore. Old is when you don''t want to learn anything new except how to be old. Old is when people tell you that you are old-and you believe them.', 23450, 0), (133754, 'Even now that he is gone I have him still, in the richness of my memories. I''ve lived my life again just telling it to you.', 463, 0), (133755, 'I had zero idea of what I was doing.. I honestly had no idea where to start. All I knew was I had something I craved to say.. I wanted to create art that lived on longer than I do. Perseverance and teaching yourself, every day through stress and hard work proves shit really does progress without you realizing. One minute you''re an amateur, knowing nothing, not even the basics. The next you can put pen to paper, write a song, and create art in such little time! It''s crazy beautiful.', 25481, 0), (133756, 'i choose to focus my energy on what I believe deserves my time, life passes us by so quickly and before we know it; were looking back at our story, make sure the choices you decide on; will give you a movie worth watching.', 3305, 0), (133757, 'Whether someone does right by you or wrong by you thank them anyway.', 3305, 0), (133758, 'Until you go and grow ‎MAD‬ with and in your true passion and purpose, you cannot enter the realm of meteority which is enemical to mediocrity.', 3337, 0), (133759, 'I feel like we have to deal with things, so we realize change! Change comes after pain and pain comes after truth. Truth is hurtful.', 25482, 0), (133760, 'Entrepreneur, let your global & generational vision start locally, now.', 24838, 0), (133761, 'Reading is a lot like fine dining... Some readers prefer just the meat and potatoes', 25483, 0), (133762, 'Deep inside of you is a ''Guru'' with the wisdom of the entire Universe!', 14464, 0), (133763, 'Ignorance is a fools castle.', 33, 0), (133764, 'A good man lives for the joy in life and the happiness of being alive, not shackled to the wants of the future or the regrets of the past.', 23450, 0), (133765, 'Sometimes the grass gets mowedat the house where the writer lives.', 25484, 0), (133766, 'If that poem idea is in your head NOW, write it down. Right now. Or lose it. For when it''s gone, it''s gone forever...', 25485, 0), (133767, 'Start with a brand new good-morning. To your husband or your wife. To your kids. To those you work with - and don''t work with. What''s the harm? How difficult is it? And it isn''t, and you know it. So do it.', 23450, 0), (133768, 'Jimmy Boom Semtex says Semtex goes BOOM! Handle his books with care.', 25486, 0), (133769, 'We all have a vision, a dream to hope for. Some chase it and some wish upon it.. Who do you think, wins? the chaser finds ways to create it, regardless of the fight, the wisher finds way to excuse it, because courage doesn''t fill their hearts.', 3305, 0), (133770, 'Reading a good book is an escape to an alternative life, writing a good book is the closest thing to actually living that life.', 25487, 0), (133771, 'You know there''s got to be a better way of life - somewhere, sometime, somehow - but you''re not exactly sure what better is.', 23450, 0), (133772, 'A man with no imagination can never inspire others.', 25488, 0), (133773, 'Emancipation from suffering is your birthright.', 14464, 0), (133774, 'She loved so much misteries tha she became one', 9, 0), (133775, 'I think I’ll feel out of place wherever I go on earth, forever. But that’s fine. I have to make my peace with that.', 25489, 0), (133776, 'Sometimes we make being happy so difficult. And being thankful such a chore.', 23450, 0), (133777, 'The details of my thoughts bled into thin pieces of paper, spread across miles to touch hearts of the people; who''ve lost their truest homes- themselves.', 3305, 0), (133778, 'Yes, its hard to write. But its harder not to.', 25490, 0), (133779, 'The hardest lesson to learn, is one where someone takes away your freedom; with out your consent... You grow, you ache, the pain never eases you just become strong, And one day you will wake up & all of a sudden all the darkness that surrounded you now surrounds the doer of the bad deed. Why...Because you forgave them, your free now.', 3305, 0), (133780, 'We live by the golden rule “do unto others as you would have them do unto you”. That phrase, unfortunately, falls short of our true ability to love and be loved. I think the best thing I can expect of any society is for its citizens to examine the most precious individual of their lot, one who they would protect with their lives and gladly die if needs be, and ask themselves, ‘how do we want others to treat this precious individual?’, the answer to which is how we would behave towards others. … This, for all practical intent, is my new golden rule. From Fillossofee: Messages from a Grandfather, by Robert Gately', 25491, 0), (133781, 'I’m proud to be a writer. I’m doing the job all my heroes did.', 14195, 0), (133782, 'Kissing just like she laughs: honest, heartfelt and heartful, she pulls me down as I lift her up , and the hum she gives when my tongue finds hers makes every one of my nerves fire.', 25492, 0), (133783, 'Entrepreneur, you''re either raising the bar of excellence or, you''re exhaling at the bar which is expensive.', 24838, 0), (133784, 'Struggles and challenges are ordinary, it''s how you deal with them that can make you extraordinary.', 25493, 0), (133785, 'I tend to be drawn to people who are similar. Very independent. And the ones who aren''t, it doesn''t work. It doesn''t last. I’m drawn to quiet people – certainly I am now.', 25489, 0), (133786, 'The purpose of life is to seek harmony.', 25491, 0), (133787, 'It’s not the destination (of seeking the truth) that creates our dignity or integrity, it’s the journey. From Messages From a Grandfather, by Robert Gately', 25491, 0), (133788, 'Dear love, for nothing less than theeWould I have broke this happy dream;It was a themeFor reason, much too strong for fantasy,Therefore thou wak''d''st me wisely; yetMy dream thou brok''st not, but continued''st it.Thou art so true that thoughts of thee sufficeTo make dreams truths, and fables histories;Enter these arms, for since thou thought''st it best,Not to dream all my dream, let''s act the rest.', 703, 0), (133789, 'Every year when i travel around the world, i wonder if it’ll be diferent, maybe one year won’t come to the show or you’ll be less festival, but what i realized during ARTPOP is that we belong together and some stories have no end. I will follow you around the world as long as you’ll have me because i love making music, i love making art and i love, love meeting all you beautiful, creative people“.', 47, 0), (133790, 'I can’t do small talk really, and that’s fine. I''ve got old friends and family that love me, thank God. I’m grateful for what a city gives you access to, but I do feel that I’m only here until I figure out how to get out again.', 25489, 0), (133791, 'People want to spend time together and I just couldn''t pretend that I wanted to do that. But now I do get it. [..] Though I still don’t do that.', 25489, 0), (133792, 'It is much better to live in poverty and graduate to the middle class, than it is to live as a king and be demoted to the middle class.', 25494, 0), (133793, 'It is a wise man who said there is no inequality than the equal treatment of unequals.Fillossofee: Messages From a Grandfather, an ebook', 1207, 0), (133794, 'Peace is not found by seeking it but in simply letting it be.', 25495, 0), (133795, 'Hate is never an option for a truth seeker. It binds, stifles, constipates and causes the gears of philosophical progress to come to a grinding halt. From Fillossofee: Messages From a Grandfather - an ebook', 25491, 0), (133796, 'If I’m lucky, I philosophize about life’s principles on worthwhile standards that meet the test of time. I say, if I’m lucky, because I could be born into a world where principles are drilled into me at an early age and the idea of thinking for myself is not an option. From ''Fillossofee: Messages from a Grandfather'' by Robert Gately', 25491, 0), (133797, 'Imagine a soldier who believes killing another human being is wrong, kills his first human being in war when he has never killed before. Worse still, imagine this same soldier has his enemy in his sites and the enemy appears defenseless. Here, he might be allowed the luxury to have that moment with himself to debate whether he should pull the trigger or not. But on another day he may not have that luxury. Imagine further, a soldier is in this situation because his father was a soldier, and his grandfather was a soldier, and he is trying to please them but, unlike them, he doesn’t believe killing people in war is right, yet there he is on the battlefield anyway where ‘killed or be killed’ leads the list in the army’s operation manual. So, he pulls the trigger anyway even though he’s categorically against killing another human being. And maybe this is the first time he’s compromised on such a high principle and he continues killing other people as long as he’s in the war and each time it becomes easier and easier until his principle, his absolute truth, is a motto not to live by, but one that is just a topic of conversation in a philosophy class or a backyard barbecue. War has changed him. From Messages From a Grandfather, by Robert Gately', 25491, 0), (133798, 'Bias rules our minds and causes us to overlook the obvious. From ''Fillossofee: Messages From a Grandfather'', by Robert Gately', 25491, 0), (133799, 'I always thought that we would be that couple in the movies but not all movies have a happy ending', 33, 0), (133800, 'We''re living tragedies, just passing time ''til our funerals.', 1183, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (133801, 'Dark now. Blacker than black, I know it. And words are tiny things in the face of all that dark and all that cold. But hear these words, little sister. Hear and know. Tomorrow is coming, just as fast as the turning of the sky. And as sure as it’s black now, the sun will rise. Always. No matter how faint the glow.', 2392, 0), (133802, 'Negative people feed off of your anger, let them starve.', 25496, 0), (133803, 'Few people ever kill for the right reasons.', 237, 0), (133804, 'You are not who you think.You''re not even the thinker.You are the one conscious of the thought.', 3588, 0), (133805, 'My wakeup call wasn’t some light switch of empowerment. From as early as preschool I feared that if I didn’t grow up to be the pretty princess men fawned over, I was a failure. That mentality was my disease. It got me raped. It made me feel dirty and devalued because my cherry wasn’t popped on a bed of rose petals. It fueled an adolescence juggling starvation and vomiting until my throat bled out and my stomach acid burned through the plumbing. It made me snort coke, smoke meth, and routinely gulp down narcotic petri dishes in hopes of obtaining hallucinogenic intimacy with junkie boyfriends. But most of all, it made me waste my youth chasing, obsessing over, fighting for, worshipping, clinging to, and crying over one after another loser. At some point, I just quit giving a fuck.', 24133, 0), (133806, 'Only those who are empty within, seek to suppress those around them', 25346, 0), (133807, 'I was curious as to how my words started circulating at such an alarming rate. After all, every author waits to be discovered by someone. Anyone. And so I found myself smack bang in the middle of the mad hatters head, and as someone put it, Tumblr might actually be worse than that. But yes, futilely, I was attempting to discover the elusive origin of my words by tracing back notes until I came across my quote right next to a selfie of a stripper, or hooker, with a fox tail butt plug... and that was when I stopped.', 25497, 0), (133808, 'Your purpose has the capacity to employ and enrich you for a lifetime.', 3337, 0), (133809, 'If time is money, how much is a lifetime?', 6269, 0), (133810, 'If you live everyday, with the capacity to stretch yourself past limitation and structure, you will find boundless opportunity is all the places that once scared you.', 3305, 0), (133811, 'Incarceration is when nobody writes a happy ending for a woman without a man.', 24133, 0), (133812, 'To those who do not see, we are the enigma of society', 25346, 0), (133813, 'You can only call someone crazy if there''s someone else who''s normal.', 923, 0), (133814, 'Be Courageous: Succeed or Fail Monumentally!', 5043, 0), (133815, 'My life views on sex, men, dating, and self-worth were sculpted with the unfiltered ramblings of a drunken misogynist.', 24133, 0), (133816, 'Time. Either you are for it or against it. So be here now. Not later.', 23450, 0), (133817, 'Fight your fears with fierce and your life becomes fabulous.', 3337, 0), (133818, 'Sometimes I feel as if I''m only a doorman awaiting the arrival of her royal majesty.', 23450, 0), (133819, 'She is young and beautiful. She has no problems with men.', 6269, 0), (133820, 'I love the thrill of impending, weightless doom...', 419, 0), (133821, 'I’m sorry I broke you. It’s just that you’re so pretty, and I break pretty things.', 11820, 0), (133822, 'Truth is, life is going shake you, it will rip you right out of your comfort zone;just when you feel settled, it will shock you with some trauma and make you face adversity in the most undesirable of ways... And here is the question of it all? What''s it all for... Not many search long enough to know but the wise ask you.. Are you going to be a slave to your journey or the pioneer to your dream, if God handed you a lesson ;he knew before your time, your strength could endure i. so next time you doubt another thought or feed your heart with negative emotions think about it... You are here, alive, breathing and if that''s not enough than you should think about what is.', 3305, 0), (133823, 'if by chance I fall; I''ll learn what I had to, get up, stand up and live the rest of my life.', 3305, 0), (133824, 'I want people to feel safe around me. Calm and at peace and I want to make people feel accepted. I want to express confidence on my own path, and spread confidence to other people on theirs.', 523, 0), (133825, 'Come, let us speak with our bodies.Teach me how to please you.I am here to learn.Let us not waste this time.It is the hour of union.ComeAnd after you do,Come again.', 3588, 0), (133826, 'You do care, you feel as though you will bleed to death with the pain of it all.', 28, 0), (133827, 'Every emotional wound is due to a lack of love. Love is the cause and the remedy. Love is always the answer.', 25498, 0), (133828, 'I gather the last remnants of the evening’s breeze, so cool and lazy within my arms, feeling it curl up like a small and innocent kitten.', 23450, 0), (133829, 'Feminism is a way of thinking and being, not a way of dressing. You know a feminist by her gaze, not her neckline.', 5789, 0), (133830, 'The best tourist is one without a camera', 3588, 0), (133831, 'Spring is a time to make up a big bouquet of flowers for someone you love, or are trying to love, or are in love with.', 23450, 0), (133832, 'Sometimes I briefly touch the life I want. My hand brushes the surface as I pass it by.', 25499, 0), (133833, 'Entrepreneur, your message, mindset and mandate is connected to your brand, business and brain.', 24838, 0), (133834, 'Listen and listen good, shitbrain. If you ever touch someone I love again, I will shove this cross down your throat and watch you choke on it. You want to know why a Prince of Hell wanted me so bad? Now you do. I’m not a nice girl. I’m a Seer. It is my job to save the people of the world from vultures like you. Now you take that back to whoever your boss is and let him come find me, if he’s stupid enough. I’ll bury you all if I have to.', 13812, 0), (133835, 'You were a pain, then. You still are. You’re just a different kind of pain to me.', 25500, 0), (133836, 'Give a reason for your existence and make a life out of it.', 3305, 0), (133837, 'down unlit ,unmarked & forgotten roads of REASON & PURPOSE', 23448, 0), (133838, '...Every word an author writes causes ripples, like tossing a stone into a pond. And you don''t know where they''ll go, or who they''ll touch, or when they might come back to you. I think everything you do is kind of like that, too.', 431, 0), (133839, 'Nobody is a cure.', 20570, 0), (133840, 'No matter what’s going on in your life, remember that salvation isn’t only something Jesus did for you; it’s Jesus living in you.', 1993, 0), (133841, 'You must really love this guy, huh? I mean, to be crying as ugly as you are?', 25500, 0), (133842, 'The best tourist is one without a camera.', 3588, 0), (133843, 'Distance is meaningless, as is time, when minds and souls intertwine.”-Gerome in CHANGELING-', 25501, 0), (133844, 'Newt...""Do it before I become one of them!""I...""KILL ME!" And then Newt''s eyes cleared, as if he''d gained one last trembling gasp of sanity, and his voice softened."Please, Tommy. Please."With his heart falling into a black abyss, Thomas pulled the trigger.', 1493, 0), (133845, 'I didn’t want to fall in love. Looking at you gave me chills and kissing you made my knees weak. You made flowers grow and fill the space in my lungs which made it impossible for me to breathe. I’m trying to drench the memories and the blood that once pumped through my veins has been replaced with alcohol. My teeth has shattered from all the whiskey bottles and every morning I awake to throw up the poison I swallowed the night before as a hopeless attempt to forget the taste of your lips. I keep hearing the sound of your voice calling out my name as if it’s something I’m not allowed to forget.', 11820, 0), (133846, 'I''ve never written a quote I feel would be suitable for my gravestone. Wouldn''t it be ironic if it were this one? Oh, and could you pull a few weeds while you''re here?', 10209, 0), (133847, 'This is the story of a girl gone mad while trying to find a little bit of love.', 523, 0), (133848, 'How far you go in life depends on your being tender with the young, compassionate with the aged, sympathetic with the striving and tolerant of the weak and strong. Because someday in your life you will have been all of these.', 14728, 0), (133849, 'Good decisions can turn into disasters when communicated poorly.', 25502, 0), (133850, 'Sticks and stones may break my bones, but your words will always kill me.', 11820, 0);
